snippet.textDisplay:
I am from Bangladesh. When I first heard this song, I thought it was in Bangla language (most of the time I only focus on music and voice, without noticing the lyrics. I admit it is not a good habit.). But then I saw that this is from Odisha and I was amazed, because I felt that I understood what the song is about without understanding most of the words. After Googling for a while I realized that Bangladesh and Odisha are close neighbors, and there are some common words in between these two languages. I understand that the Odia language is unique, but because of the common factors,  I feel connected. In fact, I have been talking with friends from different countries the SE Asia for a while (from Nepal, from other states of India) and every time I find some common word (because of Sanskrit root maybe), I feel connected. 

Love and respect from me, to all of you :)
